			<div class="item2">
				<h1>HOW TO USE IT</h1>
				<p>To start using CARGO, follow these steps:</p>
				<p>1. <b>search</b> for a term (like &quot;regulation&quot;) or gene name (&quot;p53&quot;)- complex searches are not supported yet- to obtain a list of genes or use one of our previously compiled gene list (Sjoblom <i>et al</i>. Science, 2006 or Matsuoka<i> et al</i>. Science, 2007);</p>
				<img src="img/search_results_widget.gif" title="search image" alt="search image" width="380" height="265" border="0" />
				<p>2. <b>activate</b> a few widgets by clicking either on their <b>names</b> (top left ) or in their <b>tabs</b> (top of the dashboard);</p>
				<img src="img/widget_bar.gif" title="widget bar" alt="widget bar" width="380" height="12" border="0" />
				<p>3. <b>click on</b> one of the genes from the list and watch the information in the widgets refresh accordingly (some widgets have their own behaviour for instance: iHop and FunCUT have their own clickable bars and OMIM has a hierarchical menu). That's it!</p>
				<img src="img/widgets.gif" title="widgets" alt="widgets" width="380" height="264" border="0" />
				<p>A detailed tutorial of CARGO could be downloaded from <a href="Docs/CARGO_Tutorial_v_1_0.pdf" target="_blank">here</a> (PDF: 888 KB).</p>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="contentRight">
			<div class="item1">
				<h1>ABOUT CARGO</h1>
				<p>Currently, CARGO displays biological information only  for human genes. Information for other species will be included.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="item3">
				<h1>REQUIREMENTS</h1>
				<p>CARGO works best in <a href="http://getfirefox.com/" title="Get Firefox" alt="Firefox"> Firefox </a> and other <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_web_browsers#Gecko-based_browsers" id="link to list of Gecko-based browsers" target="_blank">Gecko-based browsers</a>. It works fine now in Opera and in the latest versions of Safari (3 or above).</p>
				<!-- <p>If you use <b>Explorer</b> expect some glitches (view <a href="#" onclick="openWin('htmls/glitches.html','popup','scrollbars=yes,width=195, height=133')">here</a> known issues).</p> -->
				<p>At this point, it does not support <b>Explorer, and Konqueror</b>. We are working on extending support for them.</p>
				<p>Some widgets have additional requirements, check <a href="#" onclick="openWin('htmls/requirements.html','popup','scrollbars=yes,width=300, height=165')">here</a> the full list.</p>
			</div>

			<div class="item4">
